data.description: Step into this beautifully maintained charming home filled with history in Stanton. It's been said that this house was lived in by the doctor of the hospital that was right next door. Does the sidewalk go from the back door through the yards to that hospital? Was the office on the main floor an exam room? This "exam room" is a  great space that can be used for an office, a craft room, a sewing room, playroom, possibly a bedroom. Because of the size and location, this room can be utilized for different reasons throughout your life stages of owning this home. Check out the floor to ceiling storage in the kitchen. Display all your fine china or seasonal plates on the plate rail in the formal dining room. Cozy up to the fireplace in the winter. Peacefully swing on the front porch for a relaxing evening. Enjoy a breeze while being in the sleeping porch/sunroom on the 2nd floor. Take a look out the new windows for a bird's eye view of nature. What is missing from this home other than you making memories? The radiators and boiler, that's what. This house has central air and a heat pump, 2 units even. What a great place to live your story. Call today.
